==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Artillery wheel
<hw>Ar*til"ler*y wheel</hw>. <def>A kind of heavily built dished wheel
with a long axle box, used on gun carriages, usually having 14 spokes
and 7 felloes; hence, a wheel of similar construction for use on
automobiles, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>artiodactyl</ent>⟦br⟧
